article.headline: UC Davis 69, SE Louisiana 64 (OT)
article.story: MORAGA, Calif. (AP) -- Jesse Lopez Low scored all six of his points in overtime to boost UC Davis to a 69-64 overtime victory in the consolation game of the Shamrock Office Solutions Classic on Sunday. The lone previous victory for UC Davis (2-7) came against Stanford. Southeastern Louisiana, who didn't score a basket in overtime, fell to 5-4. After a UC Davis steal on Southeastern Louisiana's first overtime possession, Lopez Low hit his first basket of the game. Phil Rasmussen, who led all scorers with 22 points, had a reverse lay-up to give the Aggies a 65-61 lead. After Ricky Woods hit a free throw, Lopez Low sank three free throws to build the lead to 68-62 and later scored one more to end the game. Southeastern Louisiana opened the game with a 9-0 run. Rasmussen answered back with eight points in a row before Thomas Juillerat scored a pair of baskets to complete the Aggies' 12-0 run and give them their first lead at 16-14. UC Davis led 29-28 at the half and tied the game at 61 in regulation when Vince Oliver scored a basket with 52 seconds left. Woods led Southeastern Louisiana with 18 points and a game-high 16 rebounds. Chris Lee and Daryl Cohen each added 15 for the Lions.
